            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20hardest%20lessons%20you%20may%20face%20in%20life%20is%20learning%20not%20to%20avenge%20yourself.%20In%20two%20separate%20instances%20with%20two%20different%20enemies%2C%20David%20demonstrated%20the%20importance%20of%20not%20taking%20revenge.%20In%20the%20cave%20at%20En-gedi%2C%20David%20could%20have%20killed%20Saul%20and%20been%20finished%20with%20running%20from%20him%20day%20and%20night.%20Instead%2C%20David%20opted%20against%20avenging%20Saul's%20evil%20attempts%20to%20destroy%20him%20and%20swore%20that%20his%20hand%20would%20never%20touch%20Saul.%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20another%20instance%20in%20the%20Old%20Testament%2C%20Abigail%20intercepted%20David%20and%20persuaded%20him%20not%20to%20avenge%20himself%20upon%20Nabal.%20David%20thanked%20her%20for%20keeping%20him%20from%20shedding%20blood%20that%20day%20and%20preventing%20him%20from%20taking%20revenge%20with%20his%20own%20hands%20(1%20Samuel%2025%3A33).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EHow%20easy%20it%20is%20to%20take%20matters%20into%20your%20own%20hands%2C%20even%20though%20God%20has%20said%2C%20%22Dearly%20beloved%2C%20avenge%20not%20yourselves%2C%20but%20rather%20give%20place%20unto%20wrath%3A%20for%20it%20is%20written%2C%20Vengeance%20is%20mine%3B%20I%20will%20repay%2C%20saith%20the%20Lord%22%20(Romans%2012%3A19%20KJV).%20The%20devil%20may%20have%20sent%20someone%20who%20is%20encouraging%20you%20to%20take%20matters%20into%20your%20own%20hands%2C%20but%20leave%20your%20vengeance%20in%20God's%20hands.%20One%20day%20you%20will%20look%20up%20and%20the%20%22Sauls%22%20and%20%22Nabals%22%20in%20your%20life%20%22will%20disappear%20like%20stones%20shot%20from%20a%20sling!%22%20(1%20Samuel%2025%3A29).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
        {
            "id": "ot-passage",
            "type": "passage",
            "title": "Old Testament Reading",
            "api_nlt_to_ref": "1Sam.24:1-25:44",
            "value": "%3Cdiv%20class%3D%22%20NLT%20NLT%20BibleText%20section%22%3E%3Csection%3E%3Ch2%20class%3D%22bk_ch_vs_header%22%3E1%20Samuel%2024%3A1-25%3A44%2C%20NLT%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E24%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EDavid%20Spares%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20Life%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E24%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20Verses%2024%3A1-22%20are%20numbered%2024%3A2-23%20in%20Hebrew%20text.%3C%2Fspan%3EAfter%20Saul%20returned%20from%20fighting%20the%20Philistines%2C%20he%20was%20told%20that%20David%20had%20gone%20into%20the%20wilderness%20of%20En-gedi.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20Saul%20chose%203%2C000%20elite%20troops%20from%20all%20Israel%20and%20went%20to%20search%20for%20David%20and%20his%20men%20near%20the%20rocks%20of%20the%20wild%20goats.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EAt%20the%20place%20where%20the%20road%20passes%20some%20sheepfolds%2C%20Saul%20went%20into%20a%20cave%20to%20relieve%20himself.%20But%20as%20it%20happened%2C%20David%20and%20his%20men%20were%20hiding%20farther%20back%20in%20that%20very%20cave!%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BNow%26%23x2019%3Bs%20your%20opportunity!%26%23x201D%3B%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20men%20whispered%20to%20him.%20%26%23x201C%3BToday%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20is%20telling%20you%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BI%20will%20certainly%20put%20your%20enemy%20into%20your%20power%2C%20to%20do%20with%20as%20you%20wish.%26%23x2019%3B%26%23x201D%3B%20So%20David%20crept%20forward%20and%20cut%20off%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20hem%20of%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20robe.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3EBut%20then%20David%26%23x2019%3Bs%20conscience%20began%20bothering%20him%20because%20he%20had%20cut%20Saul%26%23x2019%3Bs%20robe.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_6%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%226%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E6%3C%2Fspan%3EHe%20said%20to%20his%20men%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BThe%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20forbid%20that%20I%20should%20do%20this%20to%20my%20lord%20the%20king.%20I%20shouldn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20attack%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anointed%20one%2C%20for%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20himself%20has%20chosen%20him.%26%23x201D%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_7%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%227%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E7%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20restrained%20his%20men%20and%20did%20not%20let%20them%20kill%20Saul.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3EAfter%20Saul%20had%20left%20the%20cave%20and%20gone%20on%20his%20way%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_8%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%228%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E8%3C%2Fspan%3EDavid%20came%20out%20and%20shouted%20after%20him%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BMy%20lord%20the%20king!%26%23x201D%3B%20And%20when%20Saul%20looked%20around%2C%20David%20bowed%20low%20before%20him.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_9%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%229%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E9%3C%2Fspan%3EThen%20he%20shouted%20to%20Saul%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BWhy%20do%20you%20listen%20to%20the%20people%20who%20say%20I%20am%20trying%20to%20harm%20you%3F%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_10%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2210%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E10%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20very%20day%20you%20can%20see%20with%20your%20own%20eyes%20it%20isn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20true.%20For%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20placed%20you%20at%20my%20mercy%20back%20there%20in%20the%20cave.%20Some%20of%20my%20men%20told%20me%20to%20kill%20you%2C%20but%20I%20spared%20you.%20For%20I%20said%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BI%20will%20never%20harm%20the%20king%26%23x2014%3Bhe%20is%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x2019%3Bs%20anointed%20one.%26%23x2019%3B%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_11%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2211%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E11%3C%2Fspan%3ELook%2C%20my%20father%2C%20at%20what%20I%20have%20in%20my%20hand.%20It%20is%20a%20piece%20of%20the%20hem%20of%20your%20robe!%20I%20cut%20it%20off%2C%20but%20I%20didn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20kill%20you.%20This%20proves%20that%20I%20am%20not%20trying%20to%20harm%20you%20and%20that%20I%20have%20not%20sinned%20against%20you%2C%20even%20though%20you%20have%20been%20hunting%20for%20me%20to%20kill%20me.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_12%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2212%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E12%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23x201C%3BMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20judge%20between%20us.%20Perhaps%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20will%20punish%20you%20for%20what%20you%20are%20trying%20to%20do%20to%20me%2C%20but%20I%20will%20never%20harm%20you.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_13%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2213%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E13%3C%2Fspan%3EAs%20that%20old%20proverb%20says%2C%20%26%23x2018%3BFrom%20evil%20people%20come%20evil%20deeds.%26%23x2019%3B%20So%20you%20can%20be%20sure%20I%20will%20never%20harm%20you.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_14%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2214%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E14%3C%2Fspan%3EWho%20is%20the%20king%20of%20Israel%20trying%20to%20catch%20anyway%3F%20Should%20he%20spend%20his%20time%20chasing%20one%20who%20is%20as%20worthless%20as%20a%20dead%20dog%20or%20a%20single%20flea%3F%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_15%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2215%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E15%3C%2Fspan%3EMay%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20therefore%20judge%20which%20of%20us%20is%20right%20and%20punish%20the%20guilty%20one.%20He%20is%20my%20advocate%2C%20and%20he%20will%20rescue%20me%20from%20your%20power!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_16%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2216%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E16%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20had%20finished%20speaking%2C%20Saul%20called%20back%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BIs%20that%20really%20you%2C%20my%20son%20David%3F%26%23x201D%3B%20Then%20he%20began%20to%20cry.%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_17%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2217%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E17%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20he%20said%20to%20David%2C%20%26%23x201C%3BYou%20are%20a%20better%20man%20than%20I%20am%2C%20for%20you%20have%20repaid%20me%20good%20for%20evil.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_18%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2218%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E18%3C%2Fspan%3EYes%2C%20you%20have%20been%20amazingly%20kind%20to%20me%20today%2C%20for%20when%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20put%20me%20in%20a%20place%20where%20you%20could%20have%20killed%20me%2C%20you%20didn%26%23x2019%3Bt%20do%20it.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_19%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2219%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E19%3C%2Fspan%3EWho%20else%20would%20let%20his%20enemy%20get%20away%20when%20he%20had%20him%20in%20his%20power%3F%20May%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20reward%20you%20well%20for%20the%20kindness%20you%20have%20shown%20me%20today.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_20%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2220%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E20%3C%2Fspan%3EAnd%20now%20I%20realize%20that%20you%20are%20surely%20going%20to%20be%20king%2C%20and%20that%20the%20kingdom%20of%20Israel%20will%20flourish%20under%20your%20rule.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_21%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2221%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E21%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20swear%20to%20me%20by%20the%20%3Cspan%20class%3D%22sc%22%3ELord%3C%2Fspan%3E%20that%20when%20that%20happens%20you%20will%20not%20kill%20my%20family%20and%20destroy%20my%20line%20of%20descendants!%26%23x201D%3B%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_24_22%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2224%22%20vn%3D%2222%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E22%3C%2Fspan%3ESo%20David%20promised%20this%20to%20Saul%20with%20an%20oath.%20Then%20Saul%20went%20home%2C%20but%20David%20and%20his%20men%20went%20back%20to%20their%20stronghold.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_25_1%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%221%22%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22chapter-number%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw%22%3E1%20Samuel%3C%2Fspan%3E%26%23xA0%3B%3Cspan%20class%3D%22cw_ch%22%3E25%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3EThe%20Death%20of%20Samuel%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-ch-hd%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E1%3C%2Fspan%3ENow%20Samuel%20died%2C%20and%20all%20Israel%20gathered%20for%20his%20funeral.%20They%20buried%20him%20at%20his%20house%20in%20Ramah.%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22subhead%22%3ENabal%20Angers%20David%3C%2Fp%3E%0A%3Cp%20class%3D%22body-hd%22%3EThen%20David%20moved%20down%20to%20the%20wilderness%20of%20Maon.%3Ca%20class%3D%22a-tn%22%3E*%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22tn-ref%22%3E25%3A1%3C%2Fspan%3E%20As%20in%20Greek%20version%20(see%20also%2025%3A2)%3B%20Hebrew%20reads%20%3Cem%3EParan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_25_2%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%222%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E2%3C%2Fspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20wealthy%20man%20from%20Maon%20who%20owned%20property%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Carmel.%20He%20had%203%2C000%20sheep%20and%201%2C000%20goats%2C%20and%20it%20was%20sheep-shearing%20time.%20%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_25_3%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%223%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E3%3C%2Fspan%3EThis%20man%26%23x2019%3Bs%20name%20was%20Nabal%2C%20and%20his%20wife%2C%20Abigail%2C%20was%20a%20sensible%20and%20beautiful%20woman.%20But%20Nabal%2C%20a%20descendant%20of%20Caleb%2C%20was%20crude%20and%20mean%20in%20all%20his%20dealings.%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%0A%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_25_4%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%224%22%3E%0A%3C%2Fverse_export%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%22body%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E4%3C%2Fspan%3EWhen%20David%20heard%20that%20Nabal%20was%20shearing%20his%20sheep%2C%20%3Cverse_export%20orig%3D%22sam1_25_5%22%20bk%3D%22sam1%22%20ch%3D%2225%22%20vn%3D%225%22%3E%3Cspan%20class%3D%22vn%22%3E5%3C%2Fspan%3Ehe%20sent%20ten%20